    • Constructor Detail

      • POI

        public POI(int locationID,
           String locationName,
           String address,
           int postalCode,
           double rating,
           double cost,
           String startHrs,
           String endHrs,
           String openingDays,
           String description,
           double UVI,
           double PSI,
           String img)
        Creates a Place of Interest (POI) with the specified itinerary_id, itinerary_name, visit_date.
        Parameters:
        locationID - The location ID that is essential to keep track of each POI.
        locationName - The location name associated with the POI.
        address - The full address needed to locate the POI.
        postalCode - The postal code needed to locate the region of the POI.
        rating - A metric which is gathered from all users, as an indication of the popularity of the POI.
        cost - The estimated to-be incurred expenses for every visit to the POI.
        startHrs - The start of the POI's operating hours.
        endHrs - The end of the POI's operating hours.
        openingDays - The opening days of the POI.
        description - A brief description of the POI, to entice the users.
        UVI - A weather-related metric which indicates the intensity of the sunlight.
        PSI - A environment-related metric which indicates the extent of the pollution.
        img - The image path associated with the POI.
